    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Christian Yelich** (71.87) and **Trea Turner** (70.10). **Christian Yelich** benefits from a massive 13% boost due to dynamic platoon advantages against Zack Littell, making him our safest bet for high-efficiency production. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** anchors the leadoff spot; despite facing a high-caliber arm in Zac Gallen, his elite order placement and park factor adjustments keep him firmly in the 70-point tier. **Colt Keith** (68.60) is another focal point, as he benefits from a rare combination of strong platoon positioning and the aggressive base-running environment created by Sandy Alcantara\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a key bump for our speed-oriented roster philosophy.\n\nStrategy today hinges on balancing high-floor veterans against matchup-specific upside. **Kyle Schwarber** (66.95) remains a must-start despite the tough matchup against Zac Gallen, as his elite xwOBA effectively cancels out the risk of a high-tier opponent. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Yordan Alvarez** (58.57); while his scoring is suppressed by an elite matchup against Logan Gilbert, his BvP history and lineup stability make him a necessary start over the bench options. The closest exclusion remains **Victor Scott II** (57.13). While **Victor Scott II** is a premier speed asset, his placement in the #9 hole and a unfavorable park factor ultimately saw him edged out by **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who leverages a 10% wind-out advantage and a significantly better platoon outlook against Bubba Chandler.\n\nRisks today are concentrated on the **Yordan Alvarez** and **Josh Smith** slots, both of which rely on lineup assumptions. While **Josh Smith** presents an attractive profile due to a massive SP skill boost (+19%) and favorable platoon splits against Roki Sasaki, any deviation from the projected #8 spot would force a re-evaluation of his cap usage. We are also monitoring **Hyeseong Kim**, who remains on the bench due to a brutal matchup against Jacob deGrom; his limited projected efficiency today makes him a luxury we cannot afford while protecting our game caps. Expect **Kazuma Okamoto** to provide a modest, steady floor, though he will need to navigate a tricky neutral-platoon matchup against Taj Bradley to justify his UTIL spot.",
